description:
The Dark Shark Nebula is a molecular cloud in the Cepheus constellation. Within this field of view there are two reflection nebulae, along with tons of dust, all being illuminated by nearby stars. 

To capture this nebula I used my Meade 115mm triplet apo and my ZWO ASI 071MC Pro under dark, moonless skies. This is a total of about 15 hours of data, captured over the course of four nights in June, 2020.

Technical information
_______________________________________
Imaging Scope: 115mm Meade 6000 Triplet Apo
Imaging Camera: ZWO ASI071MC Pro
Guiding Telescope: William Optics 50mm Guider
Guiding Camera: ZWO ASI 120MC Mini
Mount: Skywatcher EQ-6R Pro
Filters: Baader Uv/Ir Cut
Capture Software: Sequence Generator Pro
Processing Software: Astro Pixel Processor, Pixinsight and Photoshop

Exposures:
446 x 120s UV/IR Cut
total of 14.8 hours
title: LDN 1235 - The Dark Shark
